result.adr_address: 5/F Crawford House, 70 Queen's Road, Central, Hong Kong
result.formatted_address: 5/F Crawford House, 70 Queen's Road, Central, Hong Kong
result.name: Mr Wolf

reviews.text:
Very attractive little Sunday Roast buffet.  Bright, comfortable dining area is great for relaxing, lazy Sunday.  The young lady twisting balloon is a happy distraction for the many kids.
Plenty of protein with the Roast Beef, Pork and Chicken.  All the sides you would want with Yorkshire pudding, carrots, peas and potatoes.  A few salads and a couple of desserts to round out a very enjoyable Sunday meal.

***This is a review for happy hours only*** The happy hours are between 5pm to 9pm. I didn't have a real meal there, but it was a good deal for beers and wines. Snacks were yummy. For those who smoke, they have a balcony. Staffs were attentive and even exchanged our French fries that were too salty. Nice!

Went for the Roast beef dinner on a Sunday. We sat outside and the atmosphere was terrific including live music. Yorkshire puddings are a close second to my moms cooking. Roast pork with crispy crackling was also very good. Great value at Mr. wolf and my new fave Sunday roast spot!

Great place for good quality food and reasonable price. Deco is extremely chill and laid-back. The staff was friendly, but not overly oppressive with their presence.

Good place to just really chill, have a drink, and have some food.

It's Okay. Servers were friendly, but not very professional. Only good thing I had here was the char siu with red rice, which was very very yummy. Other food was forgettable. The brownie for dessert was kind of rubbery. Don't think I will go back
